<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Every so often, I get a pretty empty feeling of nothing and I&#39;ve been working on my next set of compositions that has one piece that I want to feel the same way so I guess it&#39;s perfect timing but I don&#39;t know many piano works with the feeling. I&#39;m looking for pieces that just feel like utter chaos and lacks stability. Just a deranged man that rules the world or is being crushed. I&#39;m not sure how to describe it. Just going crazy. Yes.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/BigPianoGuy"> /u/BigPianoGuy </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wh7srq/deranged_piano_works/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wh7srq/deranged_piano_works/">[comments]</a></span>